				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "### 1.2 List Worker Scripts\n\n`GET /accounts/{account_id}/workers/scripts`\n\nOptional query: `tags` -- comma-separated `tag:yes` / `tag:no` filter.\n\nReturns array of script objects with: `id`, `created_on`, `modified_on`, `etag`, `handlers`, `has_modules`, `compatibility_date`, `compatibility_flags`, `usage_model`, `last_deployed_from`, `logpush`, `routes` (array of `{id, pattern, script}`), `tags`, `tail_consumers`, `placement`, `observability`.\n\n### 1.3 Download a Worker Script\n\n`GET /accounts/{account_id}/workers/scripts/{script_name}`\n\nReturns **raw script content** (not JSON-wrapped). The response body is the JavaScript source code directly.\n\n### 1.4 Delete a Worker Script\n\n`DELETE /accounts/{account_id}/workers/scripts/{script_name}`\n\nOptional query: `force=true` bypasses deletion blocks from service bindings or Durable Objects.\n\nReturns: `{ \"success\": true, \"result\": null }`\n\n### 1.5 Script Settings\n\n**Get:** `GET /accounts/{account_id}/workers/scripts/{script_name}/script-settings`\n**Update:** `PATCH /accounts/{account_id}/workers/scripts/{script_name}/script-settings`\n\nReturns/accepts: `logpush`, `tags`, `observability`, `tail_consumers`. Note: bindings are NOT in this endpoint -- they are part of the upload metadata."
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
