				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "## 7. Complete Deployment Flow via REST API\n\nEnd-to-end steps to deploy a webhook Worker entirely via HTTP (no Wrangler CLI):\n\n**Step 1 -- Get account subdomain** (one-time discovery)\n`GET /accounts/{account_id}/workers/subdomain` returns `{ \"subdomain\": \"myaccount\" }`\n\n**Step 2 -- (Optional) Create KV namespace**\n`POST /accounts/{account_id}/storage/kv/namespaces` with `{ \"title\": \"webhook-events\" }` returns `namespace_id`\n\n**Step 3 -- Upload Worker script with bindings**\n`PUT /accounts/{account_id}/workers/scripts/my-webhook` as multipart form with metadata JSON (specifying `main_module`, `compatibility_date`, `bindings`) and the JavaScript file\n\n**Step 4 -- Enable workers.dev** (usually already enabled by default)\n`POST /accounts/{account_id}/workers/scripts/my-webhook/subdomain` with `{ \"enabled\": true }`\n\n**Step 5 -- Worker is now live**\n`https://my-webhook.myaccount.workers.dev`\n\n**Step 6 -- (Optional) Add custom domain route**\n`POST /zones/{zone_id}/workers/routes` with `{ \"pattern\": \"api.example.com/webhooks/*\", \"script\": \"my-webhook\" }`"
			},
